    public class FakePersistence<K,V>
extends java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<K,V>
    Fake persistence class Mocking a partially synchronized persistence key-value storage by being nothing else than a simple ConcurrentHashMap All the concurrency magic happens here - no need for explicit synchronization or locking.
